<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: EL RIO; 3 TEEN-AGERS JAILED, ACCUSED OF CAR THEFT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By PEGGY Y. LEE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Three teen-agers suspected of stealing a Lincoln Towncar in El Rio on Friday 
crashed it on the Ventura Freeway in Camarillo two hours later and were 
arrested on a runway at Camarillo Airport as they tried to flee, authorities 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 The car broke through the fence on the Ventura Freeway, south of Las Posas 
Road, about 12:20 p.m. and flipped onto its roof on a frontage road, California 
Highway Patrol Officer Curt Rhyne said.Officers responding to the accident saw 
three teen-agers running from the car toward the airport, he said. 
</P>
<P>
 "Apparently they had stolen the car two hours before that," said Rhyne, who 
was one of the first officers at the scene. 
</P>
<P>
 The trio crossed a field, jumped a fence and went through a ditch before 
running onto an abandoned section of a runway, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 "They were out of breath when we caught them," Rhyne said. Airport security, 
sheriff's deputies and CHP officers converged on the trio at the runway. 
</P>
<P>
 The teen-agers, all from El Rio, are 14, 15 and 17. Their names are not being 
released because of their ages. They are being held at Juvenile Hall on 
suspicion of car theft, possession of stolen property, driving without a 
driver's license and walking on a prohibited area on a runway. PEGGY Y. LEE 
</P>
