<P>
TEXAS WINS NO. 1,333 FOR GUSTAFSON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Jeff Conway's two-run single helped Texas beat Grand Canyon, 10-1, Friday 
night and give Longhorn Coach Cliff Gustafson the career record for Division I 
college baseball victories. 
</P>
<P>
 Gustafson has 1,333, putting him one ahead of Rod Dedeaux, who was 
1,332-571-11 in 45 years at USC. 
</P>
<P>
 Gustafson, 63, needed 258 fewer games to reach Dedeaux's mark. He is 
1,333-325-2 in 27 years at Texas. 
</P>
<P>
 Texas, which trailed by 1-0 early in the game, moved in front with a three-run 
sixth inning, sparked by Conway's two-run single. 
</P>
