<HEADLINE>
<P>
DUPONT SETTLES 220 FUNGICIDE LAWSUITS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By WILMINGTON, Del. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 DuPont Co. said Friday it will pay $214 million to settle close to half the 
560 suits against it relating to a controversial fungicide that farmers say 
ruined crops and led to sexual dysfunction. 
</P>
<P>
 The settlement of 220 of the suits is the latest effort by the chemical giant 
to put behind it the long-simmering dispute over farmers' claims against 
Benlate DF 50.  
</P>
<P>
 With Friday's settlement, DuPont will have paid out about $714 million to 
farmers with Benlate complaints, and insurance deductibles and other charges 
bring its costs to nearly $1 billion, according to an analyst's figures. 
</P>
<P>
 DuPont said the settlement is covered by previous charges to earnings, which 
total $476 million after taxes. 
</P>
</TEXT>
