<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY: BANKING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 HUD to Propose Banking Reforms: The Department of Housing and Urban 
Development is expected to release a report Monday calling for broad reforms of 
the $177-billion Federal Home Loan Bank System, officials said.The system 
provides loans to thrifts and savings banks in much the same way the Federal 
Reserve System aids commercial banks. The HUD report will mark the Clinton 
Administration's first official statement about what role it wants the system's 
lenders to play in housing finance. It is expected to call for changes that 
would increase lending to low-income borrowers and developers of low-cost 
housing. 
</P>
