<P>
BRIEFLY: AUTOS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 GM to Recall 46,000 Cars, Trucks: The auto maker said it is recalling 12,000 
of its 1994-model Cadillac, Buick and Chevrolet cars and 34,000 of its 
1994-model C/K full-size pickups.General Motors Corp. said the Cadillac 
Fleetwood, Buick Roadmaster and Chevrolet Caprice models may have misrouted 
engine oil cooler lines, which could lead to an engine fire. On the C/K 
pickups, it said, a nut was not being properly tightened, which could result in 
loss of control of the vehicle. The company said there have been no reports of 
incidents related to either condition. 
