<HEADLINE>
<P>
PINK FLOYD SHOW WAS FINE WITHOUT SCREENS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Regarding Mike Boehm's critical comments about the lack of video screens at 
the Pink Floyd concert for close-in viewing of the band ("Floyd's Back, for 
Better and Worse," April 16). 
</P>
<P>
 In case you didn't notice it . . . there was a show going on. That would be 
like saying you did not like "Phantom of the Opera," because you could not see 
the orchestra. 
</P>
<P>
 I know it is in vogue to criticize any show that is commercially successful, 
but I have been attending concerts for more than 20 years, and this was one of 
the most complete and entertaining shows I have ever seen, from start to 
finish. 
</P>
<P>
 On this event, your review missed the mark entirely. 
</P>
<P>
 MIKE MacKENZIE 
</P>
<P>
 Tustin 
</P>
