<HEADLINE>
<P>
WORD ON THE STREET SCENE IS 'FAMILY' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIMI KO, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES; Compiled by Ken Williams 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Street Scene, a two-day family art festival, will take place at Cal State 
Fullerton today and Sunday from 10 a.m. to 5 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 The free event, part of countywide Imagination Celebration activities, will 
feature about 90 amateur and professional chalk artists who will create works 
in Parking Lot D, outside the Visual Arts building. 
</P>
<P>
 "This is a great family event because it appeals to little children and 
grandparents and everyone in between," said Lee Carlson, spokeswoman for the 
Art Alliance, a fund-raising organization for the university's art department. 
</P>
<P>
 The chalk artists will try to re-create the International Street Painting 
Festival, which takes place annually in Italy. Chalk art was popularized during 
the 16th Century, when artists transformed pavements into colorful canvases 
during religious celebrations. 
</P>
<P>
 Strolling singers and Cal State Fullerton's Jazz Ensemble will perform both 
days. Dancers will also entertain visitors, and student artists will present 
weaving, pottery and T-shirt spraying demonstrations while a 
Vietnamese-American contemporary art exhibit will be on display in the Main 
Gallery. More than 3,000 people are expected to attend. 
</P>
<P>
 For $10, children can buy colored chalk to use for their own creations, 
Carlson said. Proceeds from the events, food sales and sponsorships will raise 
money for scholarships for art students and to support the gallery. 
</P>
<P>
 * Street Scene runs today and Sunday from 10 a.m. to 5 p.m. at Cal State 
Fullerton, 800 N. State College Blvd. Free. (714) 773-3256 IMAGINATION 
CELEBRATION 
</P>
<P>
 Today: 
</P>
<P>
 * The eighth annual High School Choral Festival is from 9 a.m. to 1 p.m. at 
the Orange County Performing Arts Center, 600 Town Center Drive, Costa Mesa. 
Free. (714) 556-2787, Ext 888. 
</P>
<P>
 * Street Scene, a family arts festival with chalk painting, live music, 
theater and dance performances, art demonstrations and more, is from 10 a.m. to 
5 p.m. in the Visual Arts Center at Cal State Fullerton, 800 N. State College 
Blvd., Fullerton. Free. Through Sunday. (714) 773-3256. Story, F3. 
</P>
<P>
 * Arts Festival Day, featuring circus-themed performances and art workshops 
for children, is from 10 a.m. to 5 p.m. at the Children's Museum at La Habra, 
301 S. Euclid St., La Habra. Free. (310) 905-9793. 
</P>
