 * The Pacific Symphony presents "Dances Around the World" for children at 10 
and 11:15 a.m. at the Celebrity Theatre, 201 E. Broadway, Anaheim. Free tickets 
may be picked up at the Anaheim Museum, 241 S. Anaheim Blvd., Anaheim. (714) 
778-3301. 
</P>
<P>
 * "Artventures," a watercolor, collage and printmaking workshop for all ages, 
is from 11 a.m. to 3 p.m. at the Laguna Art Museum, 307 Cliff Drive, Laguna 
Beach. Free. (714) 494-8971. 
</P>
<P>
 * The Anaheim Children's Festival takes place from 11 a.m. to 5 p.m. at the 
Koll Anaheim Center, Anaheim Boulevard and West Harbor Place, Anaheim. There 
will be live entertainment, street chalk painting, storytelling, arts and 
crafts and face painting. Free. (714) 778-3301. 
</P>
<P>
 * "On Stage at the Curtis Theatre," a variety show by and for children, is 
from noon to 4 p.m. at the theater, 1 Civic Center Circle, Brea. Free. (714) 
990-7722. 
</P>
<P>
 * "Young Masters," featuring work by student artists, opens at Irvine City 
Hall, Alton Parkway and Harvard Avenue, Irvine. Hours today: 2 to 5 p.m. Free. 
Through Thursday. (714) 724-6000. 
</P>
<P>
 Sunday: 
</P>
<P>
 * The Orange County Marine Institute is offering programs of seafaring 
stories, songs and lore at 10:30 a.m., 12:15 and 1:30 p.m. aboard the tall ship 
Pilgrim in Dana Point Harbor, 24200 Dana Point Harbor Drive, Dana Point. $4, by 
reservation. (714) 496-2274. 
</P>
<P>
 * A Victorian May Day Celebration takes place from 11 a.m. to 3 p.m. at the 
Discovery Museum of Orange County, 3101 W. Harvard St., Santa Ana. There will 
be games, a Maypole, homemade ice cream, craft workshops, storytelling and 
more. $1.50 to $2.50. (714) 540-0404. 
</P>
<P>
 * Create Your Own Craft Day for children is from 11 a.m. to 4 p.m. at the Boys 
and Girls Club of Laguna Beach, 1085 Laguna Canyon Road, Laguna Beach. Projects 
include magic wands, spin-art, sand painting and musical instruments. $2. (714) 
494-2535. 
</P>
