By CHRIS PASLES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Violinist Michi Wiancko of San Clemente and pianist Cory Yeh of Mission Viejo, 
both 17, received $800 grants from the 1994 B. Douglas Sawtelle Music 
Scholarship Competition sponsored by the Orange County Musicians' Assn. Local 
No. 7 of the American Federation of Musicians. 
</P>
<P>
 Receiving $300 grants each are William Murillo, 19, a trumpet student at Cal 
State Fullerton; pianist Chaiying Lee, 18, of Fountain Valley, and Fang-Fang 
Shi, 20, a piano student at Chapman University in Orange. Pianist Charles 
Michael Liu, 17, of Irvine, was awarded $200. Clarinetist Robert Coracevich, 
20, saxophonist Rodolfo Hernandez, 21, and bassist Danton Boller, 21, each 
received $100. 
</P>
