<HEADLINE>
<P>
EGGLESTON STATS DIDN'T ADD UP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 I read an article by Martin Henderson on a basketball computer simulation. I 
don't believe that Brea-Olinda's girls' team could ever come close to beating 
any high school all-star team.I don't know where the statistics came from, but 
I do know one thing, and that is that Jessica Eggleston's stats must have been 
manipulated by someone. 
</P>
<P>
 When was the last time Eggleston scored two measly points in a game for 
Cypress High? She was Orange County's leading scorer for the last two years. 
She shot over 60% from the field, and you are telling me that she went 0 for 3 
in 16 minutes. I know just about any coach would keep her in the game for more 
than 25 minutes. 
</P>
<P>
 Either you have got some biased coaches, or a computer simulation that should 
be trashed. What a disgrace to one of the county's premiere athletes. 
</P>
<P>
 JOHN CHOW 
</P>
<P>
 Cypress 
</P>
<P>
 Editor's note: The statistics listed for players were derived by the computer 
simulation. None were altered.  
