<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: IRVINE; PAIR TO BE HONORED FOR HELP DURING FIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SHELBY GRAD 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A couple who helped victims of the Laguna Beach fire will be among those 
honored by the Irvine Valley College Foundation this month. 
</P>
<P>
 Ed and Lisa Sauls of Laguna Beach will receive the foundation's Community 
Award at a dinner Thursday.The award is meant to highlight the achievements of 
people in the area served by Irvine Valley College, which includes Irvine, 
Tustin and Laguna Beach. 
</P>
<P>
 The Saulses spent months after the October fires helping victims obtain 
clothing, food, shelter and financial aid. They are on the board of directors 
of the Laguna Fire Relief Organization, a nonprofit group that helps fire 
survivors. 
</P>
<P>
 Other honorees are Margie Wakeham, a member of the Irvine school board, and 
Nancy Cast, a member of the Tustin school board, for their leadership in 
education. 
</P>
<P>
 The foundation will also honor the Anti-Defamation League of Orange County's 
Oral History Project, which tells the stories of Holocaust survivors. 
</P>
<P>
 The awards dinner will take place at the Hyatt Regency Hotel in Irvine. The 
event begins at 6:30 p.m. Tickets are $75 each. Information: (714) 559-3272. 
SHELBY GRAD 
</P>
