<P>
WEST VALLEY FOCUS: RESEDA; MAN GETS 9 MONTHS FOR FIRING INTO SKY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By TRACEY KAPLAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A Reseda gang member who fired a gun outside a party has been sentenced to 
nine months in jail.  
</P>
<P>
 Van Nuys Municipal Court Commissioner Mitchell Block imposed the sentence 
Thursday on Jose Francisco Mata, who was convicted of one misdemeanor count of 
grossly negligent discharge of a firearm, said Deputy City Atty.Debra Siedorf 
said.  
</P>
<P>
 "We wanted to send the message that firing a gun, even if it's true that he 
fired it into the sky, is an act that we won't tolerate in this city," Siedorf 
said. "The bullets could come down and hit someone." 
</P>
<P>
 The maximum sentence is one year in County Jail, but prosecutors requested the 
shorter term because Mata did not have an extensive criminal record, Siedorf 
said.  
</P>
<P>
 Police observed Mata firing a .38-caliber revolver four times outside a party 
in Pacoima on March 20, she said. Mata also was sentenced to another 30 days in 
jail for driving with a suspended license, which police discovered during his 
arrest, she said. TRACEY KAPLAN 
</P>
</TEXT>
