ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: SANTA ANA; VOLUNTEERS TO FIX UP EL SALVADOR PARK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 To mark the end of National Volunteer Week, city residents will gather today 
in El Salvador Park to help refurbish playground equipment, paint basketball 
courts and plant flowers. 
</P>
<P>
 The park is at 1825 W. Civic Center Drive, and volunteers are scheduled to 
arrive at 8:30 a.m. 
</P>
<P>
 Anyone interested in helping is invited to attend. 
