</P>
<P>
 Mater Dei 5, Capistrano Valley 0 -- In his first start since his no-hitter 
against San Clemente last week, Adam Harris pitched a one-hitter, striking out 
seven. Harris has given up only two hits in his last three starts. Brad 
Ticehurst hit his fourth homer in four games for the host Monarchs (13-5-1, 
8-1). 
</P>
<P>
 El Toro 5, Mission Viejo 4 -- Jake Steel hit a two-run homer in the second and 
Michael Wennekamp drove in two runs with a single in the third as the host 
Chargers took a 5-1 lead. El Toro (12-8, 4-5), who received three of its six 
bases on balls in the third inning, then hung on for the victory. 
</P>
<P>
 Dana Hills 4, San Clemente 1 -- Seth Etherton (7-0) had nine strikeouts and 
one walk and gave up six hits to lead Dana Hills (11-9-1, 6-3). 
