<HEADLINE>
<P>
GARDEN GROVE LEAGUE BASEBALL ROUNDUP; LA QUINTA WINS ON NINE UNEARNED RUNS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By TOM BIRSCHBACH 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 La Quinta continues to lead the Garden Grove League baseball standings, but 
Friday's 9-1 victory over Bolsa Grande wasn't quite as easy as Coach Dave 
Demarest would have liked. 
</P>
<P>
 All of the Aztecs' runs were unearned, and sophomore pitcher Joe Garcia (5-0) 
got off to a shaky start before four of Bolsa Grande's six errors opened the 
door in the fourth inning for the defending champion Aztecs (17-3, 8-0 in 
league) at Bolsa Grande. 
</P>
<P>
 "We took advantage of their mistakes," Demarest said. "That's the mark of a 
good team." 
</P>
<P>
 Garcia walked four and hit a batter in the first two innings, but the Aztecs 
bailed him out with two inning-ending double plays before capitalizing on four 
walks, two errors, three hits and a stolen base for seven runs in the fourth 
inning. 
</P>
<P>
 La Quinta scored the first two runs when third baseman Brian Baughman fielded 
Anibal De La Cruz's bunt and threw the ball away at third, where shortstop Alex 
Francisco was covering, allowing Joe Linck and Jim Livernois to score. 
</P>
<P>
 After Garcia's run-scoring fly ball to right field, the Aztecs loaded the 
bases and scored three runs when Bolsa Grande right fielder Kevin Michini 
dropped C.J. Livernois' fly ball. Jim Livernois, who was three for four, drove 
in the final run with a single to left. 
</P>
<P>
 "Bolsa's been playing great defense, but when they threw that bunt away, they 
unraveled," Demarest said. "Livernois' hit was the only solid hit of the 
inning." 
</P>
<P>
 La Quinta took advantage of two more Bolsa Grande errors to take a 9-0 lead in 
the fifth. Corey Fox scored from first on Joel London's single and a throwing 
error by the right fielder, with London taking third. London scored on an 
errant pickoff attempt. 
</P>
<P>
 Bolsa Grande (8-9, 4-4) scored on Dan Hendrix's double in the fifth. TOM 
BIRSCHBACH 
</P>
</TEXT>
