<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP ROUNDUP; WESTERN'S WOODS SHOOTS UNDER PAR FOR SEVENTH MATCH IN ROW 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Western's Tiger Woods was under par for the seventh consecutive high school 
match, shooting two-under 30, in a nonleague tri-match Friday at Catalina 
Island Golf Course in Avalon. 
</P>
<P>
 Woods had two birdies and hit eight of nine greens in regulation as Western 
finished with 189 strokes.El Dorado won the match with 180; Avalon had 211. 
</P>
<P>
 David Dawson shot 34 for the Pioneers. Andy Noss and Dan Syhre each shot 35 
for El Dorado. 
</P>
<P>
 In Empire League boys' tennis: 
</P>
<P>
 Los Alamitos 12, Esperanza 9 -- Franco Trani and Marco Materazzi swept at No. 
2 doubles, 6-4, 6-1, 6-4, for Los Alamitos (11-3, 5-1). 
</P>
<P>
 In nonleague boys' swimming: 
</P>
<P>
 Los Amigos 92, Katella 78 -- Matt Bailey won the 50 freestyle (22.92), 100 
breaststroke (1:09.24) and swam on the winning 200 freestyle relay for Los 
Amigos. Bryan Morris won the 100 freestyle (53.16), 200 freestyle (1:58.80) and 
swam on the 200 freestyle relay. 
