<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP SOFTBALL ROUNDUP; ST. MARGARET'S SCORES EARLY AND OFTEN IN 39-0 VICTORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 St. Margaret's scored 12 runs in the first inning and 16 in the fourth and 
defeated visiting South Gate Southeast Lutheran, 39-0, Friday in an Academy 
League softball game stopped in the fifth inning because of the mercy rule. 
</P>
<P>
 The 39 runs in the second-most scored in a game by an Orange County team, 
according to the Southern Section record book. Whittier Christian's 60 in a 
victory over Bethel Christian in 1978 is the section and county record. 
</P>
<P>
 Monica Arreola pitched a perfect game, and Monica Girard hit two home runs, 
including a grand slam, for St. Margaret's (7-2, 3-0 in league), which had 19 
hits. The Tartans, who scored six in the seventh and five in the third, didn't 
bat in the fifth. 
</P>
<P>
 In another Academy League game: 
</P>
<P>
 Liberty Christian 11, Connelly 5 -- Lynlee Vaccaro had two hits and three RBIs 
for Liberty Christian (8-5, 2-1). 
</P>
<P>
 In the Express League: 
</P>
<P>
 Heritage Christian 15, Bethel Christian 1 (5, mercy) -- Sheri Larson homered, 
tripled and doubled and had seven RBIs for Heritage Christian (7-5, 4-3). 
Larson (3-0) pitched a one-hitter, striking out nine. 
</P>
<P>
 In the Sea View League: 
</P>
<P>
 University 12, Corona del Mar 4 -- Jackie Shammas was three for four with two 
runs scored and Kari Rowberg was three for four with two RBIs for host 
University (9-8, 6-2). 
</P>
<P>
 Irvine 14, Newport Harbor 0 (5, mercy) -- Shye Nakabayashi had three hits and 
Natalie Tomoguchi had three RBIs for host Irvine (11-9, 5-3). 
</P>
<P>
 Tustin 2, Saddleback 0 -- Sarah Davis had two hits, including a home run in 
fourth, for Tustin (8-4, 6-2). 
</P>
<P>
 Woodbridge 1, Santa Margarita 0 (9) -- Jackie Sukiasian pitched a two-hit 
shutout and scored the winning run on a single by Michelle Hague for Woodbridge 
(16-6, 7-1). Alison Johnsen stole three bases and had three hits for the 
Warriors. 
</P>
<P>
 In the South Coast League: 
</P>
<P>
 Capistrano Valley 7, Dana Hills 0 -- Jodi Wayland had two doubles and one RBI, 
and Stacy Henderson was three for three with an RBI for host Capistrano Valley 
(12-5, 3-1). 
</P>
<P>
 Mater Dei 8, Mission Viejo 0 -- Patty Godwin had three hits and pitched a 
four-hitter for her fifth shutout for visiting Mater Dei (15-3, 4-0), ranked 
fifth in Orange County. 
</P>
<P>
 El Toro 2, San Clemente 1 -- Dana Gulick singled in the winning run in the top 
of the fifth for El Toro (15-8, 3-1). Kelli Bruce added two hits and a stolen 
base and Kim Martin scored twice for the the Chargers. 
</P>
