<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST; GLENDALE'S REILLY IN REPEAT SHOWING AT GRAND OLYMPIC 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Pepe Reilly of Glendale will make his second professional appearance at the 
Grand Olympic Auditorium with a six-round junior welterweight bout tonight 
against Randy Archuleta of Selma, Calif. 
</P>
<P>
 Reilly, 22, is 5-1, all of his victories by knockout. Archuleta (6-8, four 
KOs) is fighting for only the third time in two years. 
</P>
<P>
 The fight is on the undercard of a 10-round junior welterweight bout between 
Hector Lopez of Glendale and Rod Sequenan of San Jose. Lopez (25-3-1, 12 KOs), 
27, was a 1984 Olympic silver medalist for Mexico. Sequenan, 33, is 56-22-5 
with 32 knockouts. 
</P>
<P>
 Also on the undercard, P.J. Goossen (10-0, nine KOs) of North Hollywood will 
make his Grand Olympic debut in a six-round junior middleweight fight against 
an opponent to be determined. Basketball  
</P>
<P>
 Chris Perez, an assistant the past two seasons, has been named boys' 
basketball coach at Notre Dame High, replacing Pete Cassidy who resigned after 
one season. 
</P>
<P>
 Perez, a 1980 graduate of Notre Dame, also has served as the school's junior 
varsity coach the past two seasons, compiling a 33-12 record. Perez led the 
Knights to a 14-0 mark in Mission League play last season. 
</P>
<P>
 "He's come through our system and done a great job," Athletic Director Kevin 
Rooney said. 
</P>
<P>
 Perez played varsity basketball at Notre Dame for two seasons before attending 
Loyola Marymount. He began coaching at Notre Dame in 1991. 
</P>
<P>
 Notre Dame was 12-14 last season, losing to Moorpark in the wild-card round of 
the Southern Section Division III-A playoffs. Golf  
</P>
<P>
 Brandon Jones, a senior at Agoura High, has accepted a scholarship to play 
golf at San Diego State, Agoura Coach Frank Greminger said. 
</P>
<P>
 Jones finished in third place in the Marmonte League championships last year 
and missed the cut in the state tournament by two strokes. 
</P>
<P>
 "I think it will be good for him," Greminger said. "They're trying to rebuild 
their program and he'll get a chance." Miscellany  
</P>
<P>
 Saticoy Country Club will serve as one of the sites for local qualifying for 
the 94th U.S. Golf Assn.'s Open championship. Qualifying will take place May 
23. Application deadline is April 27. 
</P>
<P>
 Information: 805-485-5216. 
</P>
<P>
 The Cal State Northridge Athletic Assn. will hold a benefit auction April 30 
at 6 p.m. at the Warner Center Marriott hotel in Woodland Hills. The event will 
include the sale of vacation packages, sports memorabilia, tickets to Los 
Angeles-area sporting events and theater events. Proceeds will help offset lost 
income from sporting events canceled because of the Northridge earthquake. 
</P>
<P>
 Information: 818-885-3215. 
</P>
<P>
 The West Valley Youth Athletic Assn. is holding sign-ups for fall football for 
players and cheerleaders ages 7 to 15. Sign-up dates are April 30 and May 1 at 
Fallbrook Mall in West Hills from 10 a.m. to 3 p.m. 
</P>
