<HEADLINE>
<P>
CITY COACHES TO RECONSIDER RULE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A meeting of the Los Angeles Football Coaches Assn., representing City Section 
coaches, will be held at University High on Tuesday at 6:30 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 The group will discuss the possible repeal of a recently enacted City rule 
which eliminated spring seven-on-seven passing-league competition.Out-of-season 
teams presently are prohibited from practicing after school. 
</P>
<P>
 Before the rule was changed last year, many City schools participated in 
spring passing-league competition. However, some coaches have expressed a 
desire to return to the old format. 
</P>
<P>
 Under the existing rule, City schools may participate in passing-league 
competition from June 6 to July 17. 
</P>
