<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY COLLEGE SOFTBALL ROUNDUP; ARMBRUSTER LEADS ORANGE COAST TO VICTORY 
OVER FULLERTON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By STEVE KRESAL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Kelsi Armbruster kept Orange Coast in the game with her pitching and helped 
end Fullerton's hopes with her bat as OCC won, 3-2, in 11 innings in an Orange 
Empire Conference softball game Friday at Fullerton. 
</P>
<P>
 Armbruster (13-6) allowed four hits and two runs in 10 2/3 innings for the 
victory.She had retired 15 in a row and and 24 of 25 before Alicia Robles 
tripled with two outs in the 11th. 
</P>
<P>
 Robles scored on a wild pitch to cut the lead to 3-2. Armbruster next walked 
Melissa Graham and was replaced by Kristen Varague, who struck out Tricia 
Wedekind for the save. 
</P>
<P>
 Orange Coast (27-11-2, 14-3) has a two-game lead over Cypress with four left. 
The teams meet May 2 in the regular-season finale. 
</P>
<P>
 Fullerton (21-16, 11-6) won its first nine conference games but is now four 
back and has lost two of three to OCC. 
</P>
<P>
 Armbruster's two-out single in the 11th scored Nicole Shammas to put OCC 
ahead, 2-1. Annie Presutti then singled off the third-base bag to score Tami 
Dowlin and put the Pirates up, 3-1. 
</P>
<P>
 Dowlin also contributed with her defense at second. She reached high for a 
line drive and ranged far to her left to get a ground-ball out. Both plays came 
in the 10th. 
</P>
<P>
 Fullerton used two errors and a passed ball to score in the first and OCC came 
back in the second on an RBI double by Stefanie Ritchey to tie it. STEVE KRESAL 
</P>
