<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY COLLEGE ROUNDUP; GOLDEN WEST'S BROWN STOPS ORANGE COAST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Aaron Brown had 23 kills to lead host Golden West to a 15-11, 15-9, 15-13 
victory over Orange Coast in a Orange Empire Conference men's volleyball match 
Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 Andy Kijewski added 18 for the Rustlers (12-3 in conference), who clinched at 
least third place and a playoff spot. 
</P>
<P>
 In Orange Empire men's swimming: 
</P>
<P>
 Saddleback 172, Cypress 27 -- Tory Dober won the 100 freestyle (50.91) and 200 
freestyle (1:51.14) for Saddleback (5-2). The Gauchos finished third in 
conference. 
