<P>
COLLEGE SIGNINGS; LONG BEACH POLY GUARD COMMITS TO FULLERTON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LON EUBANKS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Guard Dion Holton, a defensive specialist for Long Beach Poly High, has 
committed to Cal State Fullerton, according to Ron Palmer, his high school 
coach. 
</P>
<P>
 Holton, 6 feet, averaged seven points, six rebounds and five assists."His 
great value to us was as a defensive player," Palmer said. "We usually assigned 
him to the opposing team's top scoring guard and sometimes even to the top 
forward. 
</P>
<P>
 "He shot 54% from the field, but as our playmaker he didn't shoot a lot. I 
would expect him to score more in a college system than he did for us because 
college play is more open." Palmer said other schools recruiting Holton 
included UC Santa Barbara, UC San Diego, Montana and Portland. LON EUBANKS 
</P>
