<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE ROUNDUP; TITAN PITCHER PARISI GETS HIS FOURTH SHUTOUT OF SEASON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Cal State Fullerton pitcher Mike Parisi set a single-season school record with 
his fourth shutout in a 4-0 victory over Pacific in a Big West Conference 
baseball game Friday night in Stockton. 
</P>
<P>
 Parisi (9-2), who gave up seven hits, including four doubles, walked three and 
struck out five, broke the record he shared with four others.The most recent 
was Longo Garcia in 1988. 
</P>
<P>
 It was the first time this season Pacific has been shut out. The Tigers 
(30-12, 4-6 in the conference) had a 21-game winning streak at one point this 
season. 
</P>
<P>
 Sal Mancuso, a senior from Los Alamitos High, hit his first home run of the 
season, a two-run shot in the sixth, and Dante Powell had two doubles and two 
stolen bases for the Titans (33-8, 10-3). Jason Gill was three for three for 
Fullerton, which is ranked No. 1 in the nation by Baseball Weekly. 
</P>
<P>
 In the Big West Conference men's tennis championships: 
</P>
<P>
 UC Irvine 4, Pacific 1 -- Chris Tontz defeated Kevin Smith at No. 1 singles, 
6-3, 6-2, to lead UC Irvine at the Ojai Valley Racquet Club. Carlos Bustos and 
Kenny Cruz added singles victories and Tontz and Bustos and Marc Tardif and 
Julian Foxon each won in doubles for Irvine. 
</P>
<P>
 The second-seeded Anteaters will play third-seeded San Jose State, which 
defeated New Mexico State, 4-1, at 11 a.m. today. 
</P>
